BEIRUT, Oct. 22 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon and Argentina agreed on Friday to boost cooperation in private sector, a statement by Beirut's Chamber of Commerce, Industry and Agriculture said. During his meeting with Ambassador of Argentina to Lebanon Mauricio Alice, Mohammad Choucair, head of the Lebanese chamber, emphasized the keenness of Lebanon's private sector to boost cooperation with its Argentine counterpart which would benefit both countries. He also called on Argentine companies to adopt Lebanon as their center for expansion towards the countries in the region. He also called for facilitating the entry of Lebanese products into the Argentine market. For his part, Alice said he will take all necessary measures with the relevant authorities in his country to enhance cooperation with Lebanon's private sector. Enditem